com.application.components.TEITextStruct

Class TextStruct

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.application.components.TEITextStruct.TextStruct
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TextStruct
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Represents an structured TEI file simplifying the manipulation.

    This structure is composed of a root node that should be a TEI label.

    Each node is composed of a list of attributes and a list of children middle nodes. Also includes the text that is present before the first child node.

    Each child middle node is composed by a node and a text that is present just after the label

    Each attribute is composed of a name and a value

    This is an example of structure

     Node
 /----------------------------------------------------\
 |                                                    |
 |            Middle Node                             |
 |          /--------------------------------------\  |
 |          | Node                                 |  |
 |          | /--------------\                     |  |
 |          | |  "SomeText"  | "Middle Node text"  |  |
 |"SomeText"| \--------------/                     |  |
 |          |                                      |  |
 |          \--------------------------------------/  |
 |                                                    |
 \----------------------------------------------------/
    Author:
    Miguel Urízar Salinas

      • createLabel

        public int createLabel(int parentId,
              java.lang.String newLabelName,
              int beginTextId,
              int beginTextOffset,
              int endTextId,
              int endTextOffset)
        Creates a new label with the selected text offsets defined, it changes automatically child nodes.
        Parameters:
        parentId - Identification number for the parent Label where the child node will be created
        newLabelName - Name of the new label to be generated.
        beginTextId - Id of the label related to the afterText where the new label starts. -1 implies that the new label starts in the innerText of the parent node.
        beginTextOffset - Offset where the text starts.
        endTextId - Id of the label related to the afterText where the new label ends. -1 implies that the new label ends in the innerText of the parent node.
        endTextOffset - Offset where the text ends.
